\f0\fs24 \cf2 cTiVo can automatically remove or mark commercials from your downloaded shows. Unfortunately, it's not a simple process, and you have some decisions to make. \
cTiVo can either "Cut" the commercials out of a show or "Mark" them. Cutting deletes the commercial entirely, while Marking means to add chapter markers, so you can easily skip over commercials in your video player. The advantage of Marking them is that if there is a mistake, you can just backup to see the whole show, whereas Cutting deletes the commercial content entirely. Also, only certain encoders (ffmpeg and the obsolete mencoder) or "Formats" are capable of Cutting  On the other hand, regardless of encoder, only MP4 output files are capable of handling chapter markers. If you choose a Format that is incompatible with one or the other, cTiVo will remove the matching Cut or Mark options from the menus. Similarly, choosing Cut will disable Mark and vice-versa.\
To find out where these commercials are, cTiVo has two mechanisms available.\
The first is "comskip", which does sophisticated analysis on the entire show and determines where commercials start and stop. As this uses heuristics, sometimes it guesses wrong, but it's pretty accurate most of the time. It takes a large amount of CPU processing, almost as much as re-encoding the entire show. This process is dependent on a wide variety of parameters, so some find this a great feature, some find it frustrating as it may miss some commercials or even delete some program material accidentally. Note that comskip can also fail entirely on certain recordings; when this happens, cTiVo will provide an alert, but continue other processing of the download. More information available at {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.kaashoek.com/comskip"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
comskip's website}}\cf3 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
