The second is called SkipMode, where TiVo marks the commercials in certain shows. You'll see this on your TiVo's Now Playing list with the \cf0 SKIP icon, which we use in cTiVo as well. As TiVo's SkipMode analysis is done by humans, it's pretty accurate, but it has some complications as well. Most obviously, TiVo only makes available some information about it, so cTiVo literally has to play the video on your TV and jump to each segment to see where it starts. Obviously this would disrupt your viewing. Assuming you want to use this process, you can either do this manually, selecting certain shows and using the menu item "Get SkipMode From TiVo", or you can have cTiVo do it automatically, giving a range of times that's acceptable to take over your TiVo and TV. Each show takes about 10-20 seconds to find the commercial points. If you ask cTiVo to do this automatically, know that it will not interrupt a recording or streaming session, only a live-TV one (as that's the default mode for an idle TiVo).\
So when you see the white "SKIP available" icon, that means we have the basic information from TiVo, but still need to run SkipMode to fill in the actual points. Finally, sometimes this process will fail, especially if you have a partial recording. Then you'll see the "SKIP failed" icon with a slash through it.\
