\cf0 Then for each show that might have SkipMode data (top 20 channels, not news, etc), we will wait up to four hours to process until the SkipMode data is available (or not).  So if you don't need the shows downloaded as soon as possible, then you should be all set. \
Note there is another difference between Cut and Mark here. As we can Mark a show after it's been downloaded and encoded, we can process the show and then add the chapter-commercial information once it is received. If it is not eventually received, cTiVo will run the marking process with comskip.  \
One last comment, if upgrading from cTiVo version 3.1.2, your previously loaded shows will not indicate whether it has the SkipMode data, as those shows have already been initially processed. If you wish to see if the information is indeed available, select the shows you'd like to check and do a right-click (or control-click) and select Reload All Info.\
